---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AI-assisted math"
  description="AI-assisted, AI-driven, and AI-authored mathematics."
  currentPath="/ai-assisted-math.html"
>
  <main class="shell article-shell">
    <article class="plain-page">
      <h1>Ai-assisted math</h1>

      <p>
        This section contains ai-assisted, ai-driven, and/or ai-authored and
        reviewed mathematics.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most articles should be considered drafts, as the math may have been only
        partially reviewed, and it could be in some cases only ai-reviewed.
        Nonetheless, I share whatever I feel could be useful to somebody, even if
        it still needs lots of work.
      </p>
      <p>
        I also aim to share prompts, handoff notes, and the original ideas that
        led the ai to the proofs.
      </p>
      <p>
        I mainly use ChatGPT 5.5 as of June 2026.
      </p>

      <section class="article-list" aria-label="AI-assisted math articles">
        <a class="article-list-item" href="/ai-assisted-math/conway-thrackle-proof-strategy.html">
          <time datetime="2026-06">June 2026</time>
          <span>Switch Corridors and Boundary-Rigid Lenses in Even Dumbbell Thrackles</span>
          <p>
            A proof strategy for Conway's thrackle conjecture via irreducible
            even dumbbells, switch corridors, ladders, and closed alternating
            trains.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a class="article-list-item" href="/ai-assisted-math/previous-copy-compression-foundations.html">
          <time datetime="2026-06">June 2026</time>
          <span>Previous-Copy Compression: Foundations and Algebraic Digit Expansions</span>
          <p>
            Foundational papers on online previous-copy parsing, extremal and
            metric behaviour, and algebraic digit expansions.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a class="article-list-item" href="/ai-assisted-math/previous-copy-compression-quantitative-barriers.html">
          <time datetime="2026-06">June 2026</time>
          <span>Previous-Copy Compression: Quantitative Barriers</span>
          <p>
            Advanced notes on finite stammering profiles, exponential tube
            barriers, and conditional quantitative lower bounds.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a class="article-list-item" href="/ai-assisted-math/lef-growth-wreath-products.html">
          <time datetime="2026-06">June 2026</time>
          <span>LEF Growth of Wreath Products with Abelian and Virtually Abelian Lamps</span>
          <p>
            A paper on LEF growth for wreath products with abelian, non-abelian,
            virtually abelian, and Heisenberg-base examples.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a class="article-list-item" href="/ai-assisted-math/a-theory-about-complexity.html">
          <time datetime="2026-06">June 2026</time>
          <span>A theory about complexity</span>
          <p>
            Drafts and notes about complexity budgets, controlled operations, and
            possible obstruction tools.
          </p>
        </a>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
